 4. Reopen FZAstro AI and launch the imaging app.
 
 This preserves safety for cameras, mounts, focusers, filter wheels, and active sequences.
+
+## Safe predefined imaging-plan commands
+
+FZAstro AI can create first-stage, review-only imaging plans from predefined composer commands. These commands combine the current Astro SITE settings, current IMAGING profile, SEEING forecast rows, and TARGETS planner picks.
+
+Supported commands include:
+
+```text
+/nina-plan next
+/nina-plan next 60s gain 200
+/nina-plan target M13 60s gain 200
+/imaging-plan target NGC 7000 exposure 120s gain 100 frames 80
+```
+
+Natural safe aliases such as `what target should I image next` and `make a NINA plan for best target` are routed to the same review-only workflow.
+
+The workflow creates files under:
+
+```text
+AppData/Roaming/FZAstroAI/imaging_plans/
+```
+
+Each plan includes:
+
+- a full FZAstro plan JSON file,
+- a Markdown review summary,
+- a `.nina-review.json` handoff file for the bundled imaging workflow.
+
+Safety boundary: this stage does not slew, center, guide, start capture, schedule a run, or execute a N.I.N.A. sequence automatically. Even if a user says “start automatically,” FZAstro records that request and still creates only a review plan.
